Novanta is a trusted technology partner to original equipment manufacturers in the medical and advanced industrial technology markets. The Company provides innovative and enabling solutions with photonics, vision, and precision motion technologies.  Novanta’s common shares are quoted on NASDAQ under the ticker symbol “NOVT” Read More →































Novanta | Investor FAQ











 







Menu







Investor Relations












Investor FAQ

On what stock exchange is Novanta listed?NASDAQ Global Select Market

What is the Novanta ticker symbol?NOVT

What is Novanta's CUSIP number?67000B104

When was the Company established?The Company was incorporated in 1968 as General Scanning, Inc. In 1999, General Scanning, Inc. merged with Lumonics Inc. and became GSI Lumonics, Inc. In 2005, the company changed its name to GSI Group, Inc. In 2016, the company changed its name to Novanta Inc.

Who do I contact to transfer ownership of my Novanta stock?•    If you hold Novanta stock in a brokerage account (bought through a stock broker), you should contact your stock broker.
•    If you are a registered shareholder (your shares are in the form of numbered certificates issued by Novanta), you need to contact Novanta's transfer agent - Computershare

What services does Novanta's transfer agent offer?•    Account Information
•    Account Balance
•    Statement of Certificate History
•    Transfer Instruction Mailing
•    Individual into Joint Tenant
•    Removal of Joint Tenant
•    Establish Trust Account
•    Change of Owner's Name
•    Change of Owner's Address

How can I contact Computershare?Please call 1-800-564-6253 and follow the voice activated instructions. To speak with a Computershare representative, please call between 8:30 a.m. and 8:00 p.m. (Eastern Time), Monday through Friday.
E-mail: service@computershare.com
Website: www.Computershare.com.
​Mail: Computershare Investor Services 100 University Avenue, 9th Floor Toronto, Ontario M5J 2Y1

Can I buy or sell Novanta stock directly through Novanta?No. Novanta does not have a direct stock purchase or sales program.

Does Novanta pay cash dividends?No.

Does Novanta have a Dividend Reinvestment Program (DRIP)?No. Novanta has no Dividend Reinvestment Program.

How can I obtain Novanta's quarterly financial results?A release date for quarterly financial results is announced via news release and posted on the Novanta web site approximately two weeks in advance.
The earnings releases are published through PR Newswire and posted on the Investor Relations page of the Novanta website www.novanta.com on the day on which the earnings releases are issued. Hardcopies of the earnings releases and the related quarterly and annual reports filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission are available to shareholders upon written request.

Will I receive a Novanta Annual Report, and if so, when?Yes, the Novanta Annual Report will be sent with our annual proxy statement to all shareholders of record and beneficial shareholders. Our annual reports will also be posted on the Investor Relations page of the Novanta website in early April.

When and where will Novanta hold its next annual meeting?Novanta traditionally holds its annual meeting each year in May. Confirmation of the specific place, time and date will be included in the proxy materials that will be mailed to all shareholders in April. The proxy materials will also be posted on the Novanta web site at the same time.

Who is eligible to attend Novanta's Annual Meeting of Shareholders?Anyone who holds shares of Novanta stock is eligible to attend Novanta's Annual Meeting of Shareholders. Please bring proof of ownership as of the record date to the meeting.

When will I receive notice of Novanta's next Annual Meeting of Shareholders?A notice of annual meeting of Shareholders, proxy statement and proxy card are mailed in one envelope to Novanta shareholders approximately four or five weeks prior to the Company's annual meeting.






 










