Lasers, Chips, Molecules And Microbes: 3 Names In Pursuit Of A Flawless Future
A world increasingly focused on microscopic circuits, light-speed communications and biotech drug treatments demands high precision. But makers of equipment able to automate or quantify the processes on which that hyperspeed tapestry depends are in comparatively short supply. That imbalance has sent the stocks collected in IBD's Electronic-Scientific and Measuring industry group collectively up 51% in the 12 months to Thursday. Among the top plays

